1rt.clickbait: Arbital path is a linear sequence of pages tailored specifically to teach a given concept to a user.

1y.title: Orthogonality Thesis
1y.clickbait: Will smart AIs automatically become benevolent, or automatically become hostile?  Or do different AI designs imply different goals?

2v.title: AI alignment
2v.clickbait: The great civilizational problem of creating artificially intelligent computer systems such that running them is a good idea.

2z.title: Value achievement dilemma
2z.clickbait: How can Earth-originating intelligent life achieve most of its potential value, whether by AI or otherwise?

36h.title: Value-laden
36h.clickbait: Cure cancer, but avoid any bad side effects?  Categorizing "bad side effects" requires knowing what's "bad".  If an agent needs to load complex human goals to evaluate something, it's "value-laden".

3d.title: Arbital
3d.clickbait: Arbital is the place for crowdsourced, intuitive math explanations.

3hs.title: Author's guide to Arbital
3hs.clickbait: How to write intuitive, flexible content on Arbital.

3n.title: Arbital "parent" relationship
3n.clickbait: Parent-child relationship between pages implies a strong, inseparable connection.

41l.title: Superintelligent
41l.clickbait: A "superintelligence" is strongly superhuman (strictly higher-performing than any and all humans) on every cognitive problem.

43h.title: Psychologizing
43h.clickbait: It's sometimes important to consider how other people might be led into error.  But psychoanalyzing them is also dangerous!  Arbital discussion norms say to explicitly note this as "psychologizing".

4mn.title: Task (AI goal)
4mn.clickbait: When building the first AGIs, it may be wiser to assign them only goals that are bounded in space and time, and can be satisfied by bounded efforts.

4v.title: Work in progress
4v.clickbait: This page is being actively worked on by an editor. Check with them before making major changes.

5b3.title: Limited AGI
5b3.clickbait: Task-based AGIs don't need unlimited cognitive and material powers to carry out their Tasks; which means their powers can potentially be limited.

5l.title: Complexity of value
5l.clickbait: There's no simple way to describe the goals we want Artificial Intelligences to want.

5s.title: Value alignment problem
5s.clickbait: You want to build an advanced AI with the right values... but how?

6w.title: Task-directed AGI
6w.clickbait: An advanced AI that's meant to pursue a series of limited-scope goals given it by the user.  In Bostrom's terminology, a Genie.

7g0.title: Non-adversarial principle
7g0.clickbait: At no point in constructing an Artificial General Intelligence should we construct a computation that tries to hurt us, and then try to stop it from hurting us.

7g1.title: Sufficiently advanced Artificial Intelligence
7g1.clickbait: 'Sufficiently advanced Artificial Intelligences' are AIs with enough 'advanced agent properties' that we start needing to do 'AI alignment' to them.

7tf.title: Minimality principle
7tf.clickbait: The first AGI ever built should save the world in a way that requires the least amount of the least dangerous cognition.

7v7.title: Understandability principle
7v7.clickbait: The more you understand what the heck is going on inside your AI, the safer you are.

7vb.title: Effability principle
7vb.clickbait: You are safer the more you understand the inner structure of how your AI thinks; the better you can describe the relation of smaller pieces of the AI's thought process.

7vf.title: Cognitive domain
7vf.clickbait: An allegedly compact unit of knowledge, such that ideas inside the unit interact mainly with each other and less with ideas in other domains.

7w5.title: Environmental goals
7w5.clickbait: The problem of having an AI want outcomes that are out in the world, not just want direct sense events.

7wl.title: Aligning an AGI adds significant development time
7wl.clickbait: Aligning an advanced AI foreseeably involves extra code and extra testing and not being able to do everything the fastest way, so it takes longer.
7wl.text:
# Definition

True in your belief, if you believe that comparing reasonably attainable development paths for...

- An [2v aligned] [7g1 advanced AI] created by a responsible project that is hurrying where it can, but still being careful enough to maintain a success probability greater than 25%
- An unaligned unlimited [41l superintelligence] produced by a project cutting all possible corners

...has the former project taking at least 50% longer than the latter, or two years longer, whichever is less.

# Purpose

This page was written to address a questioner who accepted the [1y Orthogonality thesis], but questioned whether it would still take significantly longer to develop aligned AGI than unaligned AGI (say, at least 50% longer or two years longer, whichever is less, compared to a project cutting all possible corners).

At present this page is an overview and may be selectively rather than fully expanded depending on identified probable sources of disagreement.

# Arguments

## Related propositions

Propositions feeding into this one include:

- [ complexity_of_value] (even as applied to a [minimum_pivotal_task])
- [7wm]

If questioner believes the converse of either of these, it would imply simple specification of a decision function that could be loaded into an unlimited superintelligence.  This in turn would make development much easier and would negate or greatly reduce the need for:

- [7g0 Non-adversarial designs]
- [7tf Minimal designs]
- [7v7 Understandable designs] or [transparency transparent elements] in any regard except the top-level goal system and its [actual_effectiveness actual effectiveness within the AI]
- [5b3 Limitation] of the AGI's abilities

## Outside view

7wm.title: Meta-rules for (narrow) value learning are still unsolved
7wm.clickbait: We don't currently know a simple meta-utility function that would take in observation of humans and spit out our true values, or even a good target for a Task AGI.

7wp.title: Actual effectiveness
7wp.clickbait: If you want the AI's so-called 'utility function' to actually be steering the AI, you need to think about how it meshes up with beliefs, or what gets output to actions.
